etadata, \"require_strategy_by_name\"), \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:967:            \"custom-strategy\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:1534:                    strategy_name=None,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:25:- Python 3 and the tooling required by the agent strategy you plan to run.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:55:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:77:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5`.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:102:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:122:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `basic_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` (Pi agent).\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:198:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:215:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:232:  - `strategy`: strategy name matching an entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:268:Agents are registered via `Agent.register(...)` and selected per-strategy through the `agent` field in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Supported agents:\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:270:- `pi` — default for the shipped strategies. Driven through `pi --mode rpc` by `PiAgent` (`ai_workflows/agents/pi_agent.py`). Per-turn transcripts are written to `logs/pi-<action>-<library>-<timestamp>.log` in this repository (see `utility_scripts/pi_logs.py`). Pi session files are stored under Pi's default session directory (`--session-dir` may override it via `PiRpcClient`). Select with strategy entries whose `agent` is `\"pi\"`; set `\"provider\": \"openrouter\"` to route through OpenRouter.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:280:When a strategy configures `persistent-instructions`, these logs record whether\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:295:      strategy_name=\"basic_iterative\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:325:  - `strategy` validates strategy config files using `schemas/strategy_schema.json`:\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:327:    python3 utility_scripts/schema_validator.py strategy strategies/predefined_strategies.json\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:344:The project uses registry-based workflow and agent abstractions. Each workflow strategy is a Python class that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy` and is registered via a decorator. Agents are registered in the same way via `Agent.register(...)`. Strategies are configured through `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, which defines the workflow, agent, model, optional provider, prompts, optional persistent instructions, and parameters for each strategy.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:348:#### Adding a variant of an existing strategy (different model or parameters)\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:350:If you want to run an existing workflow with a different model or tuned parameters, add a new entry to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Reuse the same `workflow` and `agent` as the base strategy, and differentiate by appending a space and a descriptor to the name:\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:355:  \"description\": \"Iterative strategy with higher iteration limits\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:374:The strategy name is just a lookup key for the JSON entry. The workflow and agent implementations are resolved from the `workflow` and `agent` fields, so `basic_iterative aggressive` can still point at the `basic_iterative` workflow without any code changes.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:376:For coding agents that support selecting an LLM backend separately from the model identifier, add a top-level `provider` field to the strategy entry. For example, Pi strategies that should run through OpenRouter can set `\"provider\": \"openrouter\"`.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:378:For different prompt behavior, create new prompt template files under `prompt_templates/` and reference them in the new strategy entry. Ensure that the context given to strategy workflows has prompt template placeholders. Prompt templates support Python string formatting with context variables (e.g., `{library}`, `{new_version}`) that are substituted at run time from the workflow context. Be sure that the workflow context contains placeholder keys.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:383:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:390:1. **Add a strategy entry** to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` with the matching workflow, agent, prompts, and parameters.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:392:2. **Create a new strategy class** in `ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/` that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy`:\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:394:   from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.workflow_strategy import WorkflowStrategy\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:396:   @WorkflowStrategy.register(\"my_new_strategy\")\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:398:       \"\"\"Description of the new strategy.\"\"\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:404:           # Implement strategy-specific workflow logic\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:407:`register` parameter is the workflow implementation name referenced by the strategy config's `workflow` field.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:411:   from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.my_new_strategy import MyNewStrategy\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:414:Importing the new module in `__init__.py` triggers the `@WorkflowStrategy.register` decorator, which adds the strategy to the internal registry so it can be looked up at run time.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:420:If the library has no dynamic access, the workflow falls back to the standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:424:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:461:  --strategy-name dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4 \\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5184-9af040d4/forge/DEVELOPING.md:472:  --strategy-name dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4 \\\n/home/vjovano